\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc\cf1\f0\fs20\lang12  Edited by @insopti /remastered, remade and improved version of @Ancel's tutorial for AMD users.  \cf2\b\f1\fs30 AMD\cf0  visible and hidden BIOS Setting Guide (Scewin)\par
\b0\f0\fs22\par
\b\i\fs30 DISCLAIMER\cf3\f2\fs28         \b0\i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                     \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                      \cf4\b\i\fs26\lang12 This guide is intended for AMD users who want to access both visible and hidden BIOS settings to optimize overall system performance and reduce latency. It explains how to disable several power-saving mechanisms, such as C-states, P-states, and other automatic power management features, in order to maintain consistent and maximum CPU performance. By also adjusting settings related to memory, cache, and integrated controllers, this guide allows users to fully leverage their hardware while minimizing performance fluctuations and system resource delays. The goal is to create a stable and responsive environment, particularly suited for gaming, overclocking, or applications requiring sustained high performance.\i0\fs28\par
Modifying BIOS settings carries inherent risks, such as system instability or hardware damage (especially if your system is already heating up a lot or with an unstable overclock). \par
Although the chosen settings are carefully selected and considered safe, results and system behavior may vary depending on your specific configuration and tunning.\par
\cf0\b0\fs20 # How to Reset BIOS by Removing CMOS Battery: {{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xey0us9Nyyo }}{\fldrslt{https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xey0us9Nyyo\ul0\cf0}}}}\f0\fs20  \cf4\b\fs28 Proceed with caution and at your own risk. We disclaim all responsibility for any issues that may arise. \cf0\i Do NOT apply all settings at once! Modify in small groups to avoid OS bricking or instability.\b0\i0\fs20\par
\fs22\par
\b\fs28 I SUGGEST TOO:\b0\fs22\par
\fs28  - Use XMP/ set XMP in BIOS (If you haven\rquote t ram oc\rquote ed). This ensures your memory runs at its rated speed and timings.\par
- use BIOS Mode "OC Genie Mode" (or equivalent), which applies overclocking-optimized settings for more aggressive performance by default.\par
- I also recommend manually tuning your CPU settings, including voltages and frequencies. This provides more precise control and potentially better performance, but requires reliable knowledge to avoid stability issues. I plan to prepare a detailed tutorial on manual CPU tuning in the near future.\fs20\par
\par
