\b\fs28 LAN Power Enable = \cf6 Disabled  \cf0\b0\i\lang1036 (\cf3\fs22 recommended\cf0\fs28 )\cf3\f2\lang12                        \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036     \cf0\fs24\lang12 This setting controls whether the onboard LAN controller can be powered down during idle periods to save energy. While enabling it reduces power consumption, it may cause delays when the network interface needs to become active again. Disabling LAN Power Enable keeps the network hardware fully powered at all times, which can slightly improve ping stability and reduce packet latency in online gaming.\par
