\fs28 Clock Power Management (CLKREQ#) = \cf6 Disabled\f0\lang1036  \f2\lang12  \cf0\b0\i\f0\lang1036 (\cf3\fs22 recommended\cf0\fs28 )\cf3\f2\lang12                        \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036     \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 CLKREQ# is a mechanism where a PCIe device requests that the clock signal be re-enabled when it needs to operate. While efficient for saving power, it can cause momentary delays as the clock restarts. Disabling this keeps the clock signal continuously active, removing that source of latency.\par
\strike\f0\fs22                                                                                                                                                                                                   \strike0\f2\par
\b\fs28 ACP Power Gating = \cf6 Disabled  \cf0\b0\i\f0\lang1036 (\cf3\fs22 recommended\cf0\fs28 )\cf3\f2\lang12                        \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036     \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 The Audio Co-Processor (ACP) in AMD systems handles audio-related tasks. Power gating shuts it off when not in use, saving energy but adding delay when powered back up. Disabling ACP Power Gating ensures the audio processor remains ready at all times, reducing potential latency for audio playback or processing.\par
\strike\f0\fs22                                                                                                                                                                                                   \strike0\f2\fs24\par
\b\fs28 ACP Clock Gating = \cf6 Disabled \f0\lang1036  \cf0\b0\i (\cf3\fs22 recommended\cf0\fs28 )\cf3\f2\lang12                        \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036     \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Similar to power gating, clock gating stops the clock signal to the ACP to save power. Disabling this keeps the clock running, ensuring the ACP responds instantly to audio-related commands.\par
\strike\f0\fs22                                                                                                                                                                                                   \strike0\f2\fs24\par
\b\fs28 SMEE = \cf6 Disabled  \cf0\b0\i\f0\lang1036 (\cf3\fs22 recommended\cf0\fs28 )\cf3\f2\lang12                        \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                                         \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036               \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036     \cf0 S\f2\fs24\lang12 ystem Management Energy Efficiency (SMEE) introduces additional firmware-level power-saving logic. While beneficial for energy use, it can add microsecond-scale delays to certain operations. Disabling SMEE removes this overhead, which can be beneficial in high-performance computing scenarios.\par
