\b\fs28 Address Hash Bank / Address Hash CS / Address Hash Rm = Disabled  \b0\fs24 Disables memory address hashing, which is used to distribute memory accesses across banks for compatibility. Turning it off can slightly reduce memory latency by allowing more direct and predictable access patterns.\par
\b\fs28 ACS Enable = Disabled                                    \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables PCIe Access Control Services (ACS), which normally perform additional checks on PCIe transactions for security and isolation. Turning ACS off reduces unnecessary overhead, potentially improving throughput and lowering latency for standard desktop or gaming setups.\par
\b\fs28 Determinism Control = Manual and Determinism Slider = Power \b0\i                \b\i0\f0        \b0\f2\fs24 Forces consistent CPU performance by preventing automatic downclocking or throttling during light workloads. This ensures steady and predictable performance, which can benefit latency-sensitive applications such as gaming or real-time processing.\fs22\par
---------------------------------------------------\par
Lower Priority \endash  Mostly stability or niche use cases.\par
---------------------------------------------------\par
\b\fs28 IOMMU = Disabled (unless virtualization is required)\f0\lang1036   \b0\i (\fs22 recommended\fs28 )\f2\lang12   \cf3\b\f0\lang1036   \f2\lang12 must be tested, after disabling it can block you at Windows startup in rare cases and will require a bios reset.\f0\lang1036                                                          \cf0\b0\i0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables the Input-Output Memory Management Unit to remove the address translation layer for PCIe devices, which can slightly reduce latency. Keep enabled only if using virtualization or PCIe passthrough.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 CC6 memory region encryption = Disabled                   \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables encryption of DRAM contents in CC6 low-power state, small performance gain but removes a security feature.\par
\b\fs28 PC Adjustment = Highest Performance / use P0 State        \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\fs24 Fo\f2\lang12 rces the CPU to remain in its highest performance state (P0), preventing any downclocking and ensuring maximum responsiveness.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 DRAM scrub time = Disabled                                \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables memory scrubbing that prevents soft errors, improves performance but risks undetected bit errors over time.\par
\b\fs28 Poison scrubber control = Disabled                        \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables clearing of known-bad memory data, risking corrupted data being used.\par
\b\fs28 Redirect scrubber control = Disabled                      \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables targeted memory scrubbing redirection, improving performance but reducing fault handling.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 GMI encryption control = Disabled                         \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables encryption of GMI interconnect traffic between dies, improving latency but reducing security.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 xGMI encryption control = Disabled                        \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables encryption for xGMI interconnect between CPUs, reducing security.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 Data Poisoning = Disabled                                \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  D\cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 isables marking of bad data in memory, maximizes performance at the cost of safety.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 DRAM Address Command Parity Retry = Disabled              \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables retry on memory command/address parity errors, improving latency but risking instability if errors occur.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 Write CRC Enable = Disabled                               \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Removes CRC checks for memory writes, small latency improvement but no write integrity verification.\b\fs28\par
DRAM Write CRC Enable and Retry Limit = Disabled          \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                    \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  S\cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 ame as above, but also disables retry, removing both verification and correction.\fs22\par
