\b\fs28 NX Mode = \cf6 Disabled\cf0  (Enable if you play Valorant or prioritize security)\b0\fs24 Disables the "No-Execute" bit protection against code injection attacks. Valorant's Vanguard anti-cheat requires NX enabled to function. Security Risk: Disabling exposes your system to buffer overflow exploits and malware injection. Performance: Negligible gains in modern systems. Recommendation: Keep enabled unless you absolutely need maximum performance and understand the security implications.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 Memory Interleaving = Channel / Die Interleaving          \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Distributes memory addresses evenly across channels (Channel Interleaving) or dies (Die Interleaving) to improve effective memory bandwidth and lower latency. Channel Interleaving is typically best for gaming, while Die Interleaving can help on multi-die CPUs for certain workloads.\fs22\par
\b\fs28 SMT Control = Enabled / Disabled (\cf7\i\f0\lang1036 testing\cf0\i0 )\f2\lang12     \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                \i\f2\fs28\lang12   \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                \i\f2\fs28\lang12   \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                \i\f2\fs28\lang12   \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036                \i\f2\fs28\lang12   \f0\lang1036   \b\fs24 Enabled \f3\u8594?\f0  Best for multi-tasking and heavily threaded workloads, as it provides the maximum number of CPU threads.\par
Disabled \f3\u8594?\f0  Can lower scheduling overhead and latency, which may result in more stable frame times in certain games.\lang1036\par
\cf0\b0\i0\f2\lang12 Simultaneous Multithreading (SMT) allows each CPU core to process two threads at once, increasing total computational throughput. Disabling it removes extra threads, which can benefit some latency-sensitive applications like specific games, but at the cost of reduced performance in tasks that rely on many threads.\f0\lang1036  so, \f2\lang12 Disable\f0\lang1036  it\f2\lang12  for Latency\f0\lang1036 ,\f2\lang12  Enable\f0\lang1036  it\f2\lang12  for FPS\f0\lang1036 .\f2\lang12   \cf3\f0\lang1036                   \i\f2\lang12         \i0\f0\lang1036                    \i\f2\lang12         \i0\f0\lang1036  \cf0\f2\lang12\par
\b\fs28 DRAM ECC Enable / DRAM UECC Retry = Disabled               \cf3\b0\f0\fs22\lang1036                   \i\f2\fs28\lang12         \i0\f0\fs22\lang1036  \cf0\f2\fs24\lang12 Disables ECC error correction and uncorrectable error retry on DRAM to reduce latency, but removes protection against memory bit errors\emdash only disable if RAM stability is proven.\fs22\par
